Edo State House of Assembly has approved the constitution of a seven-member Edo state Independent Electoral Commission (EDSIEC) to conduct elections into local government councils across the state. The approval of the newly constituted EDSIEC membership followed the consideration of a request from Governor Godwin Obaseki in a letter signed by the Secretary to the State Government, Barr. Osarodion Ogie to confirm the nominees. Confirming the members of the EDSIEC on Monday, the Speaker of the house, Marcus Onobun said the commission has Justice James Oyomire (rtd) as Chairman. While, Mrs Gladys Idahor, Uduafi Gabriel (esq), Mr.Felix Ebhota, Mr Michael Emmanuel,  Vincent Aimienota and Okekuoyen  Ehiedu would serve as members. Meanwhile, the house also passed a bill amending the law establishing the Edo state local government law and the Edo State Independent Electoral Commission establishment and re-enactment law.